{"type":"message","id":"be325269","parentId":"0176e6c3","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:26:58.227Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_9pa2zd9w03q4_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 002613\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the next concrete action.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are complete\r\n2. There's a pending TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment that needs to be implemented\r\n3. The next action should be implementing the TIC classifier on pulse log files\r\n\r\nThe key insight is that compression and causal discovery are the same problem. The next step is to implement the TIC experiment.\r\n\r\nLet me create the TIC implementation. I should:\r\n1. Create a script or code that analyzes the pulse logs\r\n2. Tests for temporal invariance\r\n3. Measures invariant/variant classification\r\n\r\nLooking at the pulse logs available, the most recent is `logs/pulse_2026-03-24 002415.md`.\r\n\r\nLet me implement a TIC classifier that:\r\n1. Reads the last 20 pulse logs\r\n2. Identifies invariants (things that stay the same across pulses)\r\n3. Identifies variants (things that change)\r\n4. Tests if invariants can predict next pulse content\r\n\r\nI'll create a PowerShell script for this since that's the established environment.\r\n\r\nActually, looking more carefully - the pulse logs are markdown files. Let me create a TIC classifier script that:\r\n1. Parses pulse logs\r\n2. Extracts content/features\r\n3. Classifies invariant vs variant elements\r\n4. Predicts next pulse\r\n\r\nLet me implement this step by step. First, I need to create the TIC experiment script.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next critical step to validate the compression-causal duality hypothesis. I need to implement a classifier that identifies invariants across pulse logs and tests prediction capability.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `experiments/tic_classifier.ps1` - a PowerShell script that analyzes pulse logs for temporal invariants, classifies invariant/variant elements, and tests next-pulse prediction. This directly advances the Phase 1 advancement goal.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # TIC Classifier - Temporal Invariance Compression Experiment\r\n# Tests hypothesis: causal structure = invariant structure\r\n# Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [int]$PulseCount = 20,\r\n    [string]$LogDir = \"logs\",\r\n    [string]$OutputFile = \"research/TIC_RESULTS.md\"\r\n)\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\r\n$startTime = Get-Date\r\n\r\nfunction Get-PulseLogs {\r\n    $logs = Get-ChildItem -Path $LogDir -Filter \"pulse_*.md\" | Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending | Select-Object -First $PulseCount\r\n    return $logs\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction Parse-PulseLog {\r\n    param([string]$Path)\r\n    \r\n    $content = Get-Content $Path -Raw\r\n    \r\n    # Extract key sections using regex\r\n    $sections = @{\r\n        Goals = [regex]::Matches($content, '(?s)(?<=## Active\\n).*?(?=\\n## )') | ForEach-Object { $_.Value.Trim() }\r\n        Pending = [regex]::Matches($content, '(?s)(?<=## Pending\\n).*?(?=\\n### |$)') | ForEach-Object { $_.Value.Trim() }\r\n        Observation = [regex]::Match($content, '(?<=### OBSERVATION\\n).*?(?=\\n### )').Value.Trim()\r\n        Action = [regex]::Match($content, '(?<=### ACTION\\n).*?(?=\\n### )').Value.Trim()\r\n        Mutation = [regex]::Match($content, '(?<=### MUTATION\\n).*?(?=```)').Value.Trim()\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    return $sections\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction Extract-InvariantCandidates {\r\n    param([array]$AllPulseData)\r\n    \r\n    # HashSet to track potential invariants\r\n    $candidatePool = @{}\r\n    \r\n    foreach ($pulse in $AllPulseData) {\r\n        # Goals section - highest value for invariants\r\n        foreach ($goal in $pulse.Goals) {\r\n            if ($candidatePool.ContainsKey($goal)) {\r\n                $candidatePool[$goal].Count++\r\n            } else {\r\n                $candidatePool[$goal] = @{ Text = $goal; Count = 1; Category = \"Goal\" }\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n        \r\n        # Pending items\r\n        foreach ($pending in $pulse.Pending) {\r\n            if ($candidatePool.ContainsKey($pending)) {\r\n                $candidatePool[$pending].Count++\r\n            } else {\r\n                $candidatePool[$pending] = @{ Text = $pending; Count = 1; Category = \"Pending\" }\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    return $candidatePool\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction ClassifyInvariantVariant {\r\n    param($Candidates, [int]$TotalPulses)\r\n    \r\n    $threshold = [math]::Ceiling($TotalPulses * 0.5)  # 50% threshold\r\n    $invariants = @()\r\n    $variants = @()\r\n    \r\n    foreach ($key in $Candidates.Keys) {\r\n        $c = $Candidates[$key]\r\n        if ($c.Count -ge $threshold) {\r\n            $invariants += @{\r\n                Text = $c.Text\r\n                Persistence = $c.Count / $TotalPulses\r\n                Category = $c.Category\r\n            }\r\n        } else {\r\n            $variants += @{\r\n                Text = $c.Text\r\n                Persistence = $c.Count / $TotalPulses\r\n                Category = $c.Category\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    return @{\r\n        Invariants = $invariants\r\n        Variants = $variants\r\n        ClassificationRate = if (($invariants.Count + $variants.Count) -gt 0) { \r\n            ($invariants.Count + $variants.Count) / $TotalPulses \r\n        } else\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 00:26:37\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774326418225}}
