{"type":"message","id":"eca1e9f3","parentId":"9b9959ea","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:27:00.796Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_4ucznandh21l_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"experiments/tic_classifier.ps1\n---\n[NEW_FILE]\n---\n# TIC Classifier - Temporal Invariance Compression Experiment\n# Tests hypothesis: causal structure = invariant structure\n# Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\n\nparam(\n    [int]$PulseCount = 20,\n    [string]$LogDir = \"logs\",\n    [string]$OutputFile = \"research/TIC_RESULTS.md\"\n)\n\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\n$startTime = Get-Date\n\nfunction Get-PulseLogs {\n    $logs = Get-ChildItem -Path $LogDir -Filter \"pulse_*.md\" | Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending | Select-Object -First $PulseCount\n    return $logs\n}\n\nfunction Parse-PulseLog {\n    param([string]$Path)\n    \n    $content = Get-Content $Path -Raw\n    \n    # Extract key sections using regex\n    $sections = @{\n        Goals = [regex]::Matches($content, '(?s)(?<=## Active\\n).*?(?=\\n## )') | ForEach-Object { $_.Value.Trim() }\n        Pending = [regex]::Matches($content, '(?s)(?<=## Pending\\n).*?(?=\\n### |$)') | ForEach-Object { $_.Value.Trim() }\n        Observation = [regex]::Match($content, '(?<=### OBSERVATION\\n).*?(?=\\n### )').Value.Trim()\n        Action = [regex]::Match($content, '(?<=### ACTION\\n).*?(?=\\n### )').Value.Trim()\n        Mutation = [regex]::Match($content, '(?<=### MUTATION\\n).*?(?=\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774326420795}}
{"type":"message","id":"14d6c33d","parentId":"eca1e9f3","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:27:07.914Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The mutation was created. Now let me also check if there's a rejected mutation from the previous cycle.","thinkingSignature":"cdc2a5fd43eba0b6a2b1249424d9495d5fb20d57eba4518f154eb0b11c2ca4a2"},{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n## Sandbox Pulse Summary — 2026-03-24 00:26 UTC\n\n**Cycle:** 7 files changed, +314 insertions, -124 deletions\n\n### What happened\n1. **Previous mutation rejected** (`2026-03-24 002415.mutation`) — moved to `mutations/rejected/`\n2. **New mutation proposed** — `experiments/tic_classifier.ps1`\n3. **New session log created** — `memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 002613.md`\n\n### OBSERVATION (from pulse agent)\n> The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next critical step to validate the **compression-causal duality hypothesis**. Need to implement a classifier that identifies invariants across pulse logs and tests prediction capability.\n\n### Applied Mutation — `experiments/tic_classifier.ps1` (NEW)\nA PowerShell script for the **TIC Classifier** experiment:\n- Parses last 20 pulse logs, extracting Goals, Pending, Observation, Action, Mutation sections\n- Extracts invariant candidates (items appearing in ≥50% of pulses)\n- Classifies elements as **Invariant** (high persistence) or **Variant** (low persistence)\n- Tests **next-pulse prediction** using discovered invariants\n- Targets: >70% classification rate, >60% prediction accuracy\n\n### For Next Cycle\n- 1 proposed mutation waiting (`2026-03-24 002613.mutation`)\n- TIC classifier needs to be run to validate Phase 1 advancement against the duality hypothesis"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2510,"output":342,"cacheRead":11954,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14806,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop",